"{'model': 'mistral:latest', 'response': '\"{ \\\\\"title\\\\\": \\\\\"Reverse Words in a Sentence\\\\\", \\\\\"description\\\\\": \\\\\"Write a function `reverse_words` that takes a string as input and returns the same string with the words reversed (i.e., each word is written in reverse order). The sentence may contain letters, numbers, spaces, commas, periods, and question marks. Words are separated by any number of whitespace characters.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Function Signature\\\\\\\\n```python\\\\\\\\ndef reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Input\\\\\\\\n- `s` (str): A string containing words separated by one or more spaces, commas, periods, and question marks.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Output\\\\\\\\n- Returns a new string where each word is written in reverse order.\\\\\", \\\\\"code\\\\\": \\\\\"def reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n    # Split the sentence into a list of words\\\\\\\\n    words = s.split()\\\\\\\\n    # Reverse each word and join them back together\\\\\\\\n    return \\' \\'.join(word[::-1] for word in words)\\\\\", \\\\\"tests\\\\\": [\\\\\"assert reverse_words(\\'Hello, World!\\') == \\'olleH ,dlroW!\\'\\\\\", \\\\\"assert reverse_words(\\'I am learning Python\\') == \\'tnap ym I ma lrehtyP\\'\\\\\"] }\"'}"